OL,3,C'I didn't know I was a young carer
OL,4,Cuntil my late teens ` it was my normal'
OL,6,F"I think this is the first time I've
OL,7,Fspoken publicly about being a young
OL,8,Fcarer, I think that's because there
OL,9,Fwas a stigma growing up," he said.
OL,11,F"I felt I had to keep it a little bit
OL,12,Fof a secret.
OL,14,F"My friends were doing all these
OL,15,Famazing things, going for meals, going
OL,16,Fto parties, and I was always on the
OL,17,Fbackfoot because I could not do that
OL,18,Fand I never wanted to let them know
OL,19,Fthere was a reason why I couldn't."
